---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy | Websiteli"
  description="Privacy policy for Websiteli visitors, contact form submissions, analytics, pricing, and inquiry handling."
  canonicalPath="/privacy/"
>
  <main class="simple-page section-shell">
    <p class="eyebrow">Privacy Policy</p>
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last updated:</strong> 24 June 2026</p>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>1. Who We Are</h2>
      <p>
        Websiteli provides website, analytics, automation, and AI setup services for small businesses. For privacy questions,
        contact us at <a href="mailto:jenifer.ciuciu-kiss@websiteli.ch">jenifer.ciuciu-kiss@websiteli.ch</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>2. Personal Data We Collect</h2>
      <p>We collect personal data only when it is needed to operate the website, respond to inquiries, or improve our services.</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Contact form data: name, email address, phone number, company, selected package, message, and project details.</li>
        <li>Newsletter data: email address, subscription consent, and subscription metadata.</li>
        <li>Inquiry metadata: language, source page, current URL, referrer, campaign parameters, selected demo or example project, and timestamp.</li>
        <li>Pricing metadata: selected package, pricing market, currency, and price shown at the time of inquiry.</li>
        <li>Technical data: browser user agent and basic security/log data.</li>
        <li>Analytics data: page views, events, device/browser information, approximate location, and interaction data collected through Google Analytics.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>3. Why We Use Personal Data</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To reply to requests and provide a digital audit, quote, or discovery call.</li>
        <li>To send newsletter emails when someone subscribes.</li>
        <li>To understand which package, demo, or project concept the inquiry relates to.</li>
        <li>To record the pricing context shown to the visitor when an inquiry is submitted.</li>
        <li>To improve website content, performance, analytics, marketing, and service quality.</li>
        <li>To protect the website from spam, abuse, and technical issues.</li>
        <li>To comply with legal, accounting, and administrative obligations.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>4. Legal Bases</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on the situation, we process personal data because it is necessary to respond to your request, because we have
        a legitimate interest in operating and improving our website and business, because you consent to specific processing,
        or because we must comply with legal obligations.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>5. Contact Forms</h2>
      <p>
        When you submit a form, you must confirm that you accept this privacy policy. We use your form data to respond to your
        inquiry and may follow up by email or phone about the project you requested. Please do not send sensitive personal data
        through the form.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>6. Newsletter</h2>
      <p>
        When you subscribe to the newsletter, we use your email address to send Websiteli updates about websites, automation,
        analytics, and AI. You can unsubscribe or ask us to remove your email address at any time.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>7. Analytics and Tracking</h2>
      <p>
        We use Google Analytics with the measurement ID <strong>G-TGZY875FGJ</strong> to understand how visitors use the website.
        Analytics helps us measure page views, demo interactions, contact form events, traffic sources, and website performance.
        Google may process analytics data according to its own terms and privacy documentation.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>8. Service Providers</h2>
      <p>We may use trusted providers to operate the website and handle inquiries, including:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Website hosting and deployment providers.</li>
        <li>Google Analytics and Google services.</li>
        <li>Form handling, email, spreadsheet, or CRM tools used to receive and manage inquiries.</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>9. International Transfers</h2>
      <p>
        Some service providers may process data outside Switzerland or the European Economic Area. Where required, we rely on
        appropriate contractual or legal safeguards for such transfers.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>10. Retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep inquiry data only as long as reasonably needed to respond, prepare offers, manage the relationship, and meet
        legal or accounting obligations. If no business relationship follows, we may delete or archive inquiry data after it is
        no longer needed.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>11. Your Rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on applicable law, you may request access, correction, deletion, restriction, objection, portability, or
        withdrawal of consent. You may also have the right to complain to a competent data protection authority.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>12. Security</h2>
      <p>
        We use reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect personal data. No website or internet transmission is
        completely secure, but we aim to keep data access limited to what is necessary.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="policy-section">
      <h2>13. Updates</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this privacy policy when the website, services, providers, or legal requirements change. The updated date
        at the top of this page shows the current version.
      </p>
    </section>
  </main>
</Layout>
